  "sections": {
    "Description": "The Centipede shares the movement and health of theFirefly, but is armed with an acidic attack that appliesA.C.I.D.to the targeted tile and the two tiles perpendicular to the direction of the projectile.\nCentipedes cannot appear on the first island and are limited to two spawns, includingits alpha, per mission.",
    "Strategy": "If you can safely keep a Centipede alive, its A.C.I.D. can be useful for neutralizing higher-health enemies, such as Alpha Vek or Beetles. Since they attack 3 tiles side-by-side, Centipedes can somewhat be reliably baited into attacking your Mechs if you entice them with multiple targets. If you can't convince a Centipede to hit Vek that are already on the board, try to encourage it to target the area of the board where Vek are emerging, since Vek that emerge on A.C.I.D. squares will immediately receive the A.C.I.D. status.\nIf a Centipede's attack goes off the edge of the map, it is considered to hit the very last tile and will still cause damage and area of effect damage."
