  "full_text": "Centipede\nDetails\nHealth\n3\nMove\n2\nSystems\nAcidic Vomit\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nLaunch a volatile mass of goo, dealing 1 damage and applying A.C.I.D. on nearby units.\nThe\nCentipede\nis a rare\nVek\nfrom\nInto The Breach\n.\nDescription\n[\n]\nThe Centipede shares the movement and health of the\nFirefly\n, but is armed with an acidic attack that applies\nA.C.I.D.\nto the targeted tile and the two tiles perpendicular to the direction of the projectile.\nCentipedes cannot appear on the first island and are limited to two spawns, including\nits alpha\n, per mission.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nIf a Centipede's attack goes off screen, it still causes damage.\nIf you can safely keep a Centipede alive, its A.C.I.D. can be useful for neutralizing higher-health enemies, such as Alpha Vek or Beetles. Since they attack 3 tiles side-by-side, Centipedes can somewhat be reliably baited into attacking your Mechs if you entice them with multiple targets. If you can't convince a Centipede to hit Vek that are already on the board, try to encourage it to target the area of the board where Vek are emerging, since Vek that emerge on A.C.I.D. squares will immediately receive the A.C.I.D. status.\nIf a Centipede's attack goes off the edge of the map, it is considered to hit the very last tile and will still cause damage and area of effect damage.\nv\n\u00b7\nd\n\u00b7\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n\u2022\nBlobber\n\u2022\nBurrower\n\u2022\nCentipede\n\u2022\nCrab\n\u2022\nDigger\n\u2022\nFirefly\n\u2022\nHornet\n\u2022\nLeaper\n\u2022\nScarab\n\u2022\nScorpion\n\u2022\nSpider\n\u2022\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n\u2022\nGastropod\n\u2022\nMosquito\n\u2022\nMoth\n\u2022\nPlasmodia\n\u2022\nStarfish\n\u2022\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n\u2022\nAlpha Blobber\n\u2022\nAlpha Burrower\n\u2022\nAlpha Centipede\n\u2022\nAlpha Crab\n\u2022\nAlpha Digger\n\u2022\nAlpha Firefly\n\u2022\nAlpha Hornet\n\u2022\nAlpha Leaper\n\u2022\nAlpha Scarab\n\u2022\nAlpha Scorpion\n\u